  "title": "OcularLDT",
  "description": "OcularLDT is a neuroimaging dataset containing eye-tracking and MEG recordings acquired during a lexical decision task with ocular monitoring. The dataset provides synchronized measurements of oculomotor behavior and brain activity, enabling investigation of the relationship between eye movements and linguistic processing during word recognition tasks.",
